come a gutser
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:have a heavy fall; come a cropper, make a mistake; fail. (Air Force slang to crash)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [1918 Chron NZEF 1919 War Slang 1925 F and G. to 1957 Godboy, 1960 Crump GKM.; AC 191; so P `both low'.] cf. greaser. Also spelt gutzer.
